To the honourable the Knights, citizens and burgesses, in Parliament assembled. May it please your honours; the last sessions of Parliament I presented the Honourable the Commons in Parliament then sitting, with proposals for setting up a national land-bank in favour of the freeholders and trading part of the kingdom, ... Briscoe, John, fl. 1695.
1 sheet (2 p.).
s.n., [London? : 1695]
Dated and signed: Decemb. 2. 1695. John Briscoe. Page 2 has title "A short account of the national land-bank." Reproduction of original in the British Library.
